          Important Links



   State Allocation Board Monthly Construction Cost Index  (History).
   CalGold for "one-stop" state, local, regional, and federal permit,
   licensing, and tax requirements.
   The California State Employment Development Department provides a
   listing of tax seminars they offer to help businesses.
   Other California Department of Consumer Affairs Agencies.
   International Conference of Building Officials.
   Go to the State Personnel Board for getting and completing a State
   application.
   Go to the Department of Industrial Relations, Division of Occupational
   Safety and Health (Cal/OSHA), for information on asbestos registration
   requirements.
   Go to the Department of Health Services, Lead Poisoning Prevention
   Branch, to get information on lead accreditation and certification
   programs, to find a certified lead professional, or to obtain general
   information on lead related issues.
   Go to the Department of Industrial Relations, Division of
   Apprenticeship Standards, for information regarding the Electrical
   Certification Program (AB 931).

